PRAWN FRIED RICE ?????

Flavory fried rice??
Homemade prawn fried rice?

INGREDIENTS
??1Tbsp-veg oil
??2cloves 
??2 garlic crushed
??1 -beans,capsicum chopped
?? 2- chopped onion
??1 green capsicum chopped
??400g prawn peeled and deveined
??Cooked white rice(basmathi)
??2-tbsp soya sauce
??2-tbsp tomato sauce
??1 large egg ,whisked 
??Coriander chopped for serving 

STEPS
In a medium pan over medium heat, heat oil. Add garlic and stir for one minute. Add carrots ,beans , capsicum and saute 3 minutes, then add prawns and cook, 4 minutes, or until pink stirring occasionally.

Stir in rice and  saute all  ingredients ,add pepper (optional)and saute it all thoroughly ,add soy sauce and  toss

Push rice to one side of the pan and add the egg. Stir egg constantly until almost fully cooked, then fold into rice mixture. 
Add tomato sauce for tangy taste and garnish with some chopped coriander

The main ingredient of yakhni pulao is the yakhni(broth/stock) that is made from aromatic spices and condiments and the meat, boiled, and then adding the soaked rice into the broth. 

A pretty decent option to choose as an alternative for biryani.

ARTISTS LOCKED IN

Mehneer Sudan
Dancer  Delhi

The school I work at as a dance teacher had started online classes well before the official lockdown. It was on top of the game, finding ways to make the transition to online learning as smooth as possible. Parents, teachers & even students reached out to support one another with empathy.
While being grateful for my privileges, I was not blind to what the rest of the country was facing. The surrounding hopelessness & misery was heart-wrenching. In this environment, I was grateful to be safe and secure at home. Out of this gratitude came the need to start living in the moment and enjoy doing little things. I started doing things I had put off for years. My whole professional life as a dance practitioner has been ridden with self-doubt and anxiety. I would think about doing things rather than risking doing them and having to face judgment and rejection, except on a few occasions. 
While I have overcome some of these fears in my lifetime, this lockdown however unleashed the artiste in me! I was on a roll; making videos, started an FB page, a secret blog for just my peace of mind, at my own pace with no desire to make it reach people!  I put my bathroom singing out in public, something I had never ever imagined I would do! I had the luxury to do little inconsequential things, as my income was secure. I am deeply saddened by the cost the world has had to pay during this lockdown, but it has been a period of growth for me. I am horrified at the thought of a fully technology-driven world, but I have personally reaped its’ benefits.

@mehneer  is a Performing Artist, Choreographer & Educator specializing in Contemporary & Jazz Dance. A founder member of Gati Dance Forum Delhi, she has presented her work at different festivals & taught at dance academies and schools in Delhi, Mumbai, UK, & Cambodia. She shares her work titled Reminiscing.

?‍?? Complete a 10-Minute Exercise Warm-Up ?

One reason we avoid exercise is the way we view it—as a means to an end rather than an enjoyable activity on its own. Exercise can easily become a mindfulness activity if you shift your thoughts about how you approach it.

If you see it as a way to connect with your body and become more aware of your own physical abilities, you can lessen some of your resistance to it. For many people, simply initiating exercise for just a few minutes is enough to get the ball rolling. Just beginning anything you mentally resist is 95% of the battle.

If you don’t have time for a full exercise routine in the morning, just devote ten minutes to moving and warming up your body to get your blood and energy flowing.

When I went to Scotland, we were 3 brown travelers, no white person to signal "we come in peace." As a brown-skinned traveler, in the USA I'm acutely aware of racism and consider safety when assessing travel destinations (and dignity, because who wants to pay to get treated like shit?). This came to mind as yesterday I was turned away from an UWS restaurant 4 blocks from my home. I've learned the hard way to consider safety when traveling, especially in the south. I'll never forget being nearly hate-crimed at a gas stop in West Virginia and didn't think much of my brother bringing a white companion on each of his cross-country road trips for safety. 

Scotland 2017 was my first time in Europe; EVERY SINGLE person I spoke with about 'traveling while brown' in Europe had a story. 
- The Spanish call Central American travelers "tercero-mundiales" (3rd worlders)
- Greece came up the most in anecdotal negative experiences...

Basically I had low expectations, I've been treated like shit in Manhattan all the time, but low and below in Scotland I had zero experiences of micro-aggressions aka low-key racism, nor scary encounters with armed white men (this has happened to me in upstate NY, WV and Wisconsin). 

It may seem super basic but it was so unusual to be treated kindly everywhere we went that we fell in love with the Scottish highlands. Now that American passports are getting a taste of our own medicine, we will just have to pinterest away until la prxima ?

It’s so easy to make and literally takes just 20 mins. 20 mins for real and not like those 2 minute noodles that say 2 mins but take forever to cook ?
Just 2 tips from my side:
1. Use coconut oil and shallots if you want the authentic taste. 
2. Do not let the buttermilk boil.

VIRTUAL SHOOT

When this year started, I think, no one would have thought about the term Virtual Shoot. Then horror which we used to read in past came in reality for this generation... Pandemic. 
Lockdown was imposed in short interval notice and in a snap sound of fingers, many found themselves jobless, trapped inside. Privileged as me just had to get ourselves keep confined to our spaces. Real struggle was for them whose life started daily with sunrise and bread earned by long day hard work. Now there was no work.
As a photographers' perspective, shoots got cancelled, project delayed or denied. After a few days of not shooting, we started searching way to pursue passion. Business meetings started on conference video calls. Few photographers came with a temporary solution of shooting on video calls. Facetime shoots, WhatsApp Call shoots, Google video shoots, Skype shoot came in existence... in a shell, Virtual Shoots. Ofcourse not good as actual shoot, but "...dil ko khush rakhne ko ghalib ye khayal achchha hai...", it became a trend amongst photographers.
After initial denial, me too thought to give it a try. Talked to few people connected with me. Now I am sharing few results. 
I won't call myself as Photographer for these shots, just a director.
